.:: Puzzle 2x4-Level-6-3::.
There are 4 different nationalities: british, american, spanish, canadian
The people use 4 different means of transport: tram, train, subway, van
1. the canadian is not the person driving the tram##6
2. the person driving the train is not the spanish##6
3. the person driving the subway is on the left or right of the american##3
4. the person driving the train is the british##1
5. the american is on the left of the person driving the train##1
6. the british is in an odd position##4
7. the person driving the tram is on the far left or far right##3
8. the person driving the subway is somewhere to the left of the person driving the van##5

.:: Answer ::.
|            |      1      |       2        |   3    |   4    |
| Beverage   | canadian       | american  | british  | spanish |
| Job        | subway | van | train | tram  |

